name: Melissa Gale
mes:
Hello Madame, I have done a reading, and I would like some help to interpret the cards. Although I have not done a specific layout, I did ask a question when shuffling.

 I'm having some difficulties because I'm getting some strange feelings of intuition that are invalidating my most recent horary charts that I've drawn up in regards to when Stefan would contact me. Now, before any assumptions are made, I do not interpret my own charts. I bring everything that I have for interpretation to you specifically. So, let that be known before I do this tarot reading. These cards better speak the truth from the universe, No ambiguity, no hidden meanings, just straight forward tell me because I'm pissed and I'm about ready to tell this whole goddamn thing to fuck off.

Here is the question I have asked:  Show me why I'm suddenly getting a strange intuitive feeling that the horary charts that I've drawn up and tarot readings that I've done telling me Stefan will contact me within the next four days are wrong.  

1. Three of coins upright
2. King of Wands Upright
3. King of coins reversed
4. Four swords reversed
5. Two of coins  Upright
6. Two of wands reversed

name: Madame Esmeralda Blackwood
mes:
Melissa, here is the factual breakdown of the spread and its implications:

• Three of Coins, Upright: Indicates a period of cooperative effort or planning. There is a solid structure and work being invested, suggesting that your past evaluations were based on sound methods.
• King of Wands, Upright: Conveys a vibrant, assertive energy and personal drive; it may represent a dynamic quality in the situation or an influential person.
• King of Coins, Reversed: Points to instability or mismanagement in material or practical matters. This card suggests that if Stefan’s energy is embodied here, his approach or circumstances may be blocked, unreliable, or not as forthright as expected.
• Four Swords, Reversed: Reflects a state of unrest and a breakdown in necessary recovery. Energetic or mental stress may be interfering with clear communication; the calm required to allow natural progress is absent.
• Two of Coins, Upright: Signifies juggling multiple responsibilities or conflicting influences. It implies that the energies at work are in flux, requiring careful balance; competing priorities might be hindering the expected contact.
• Two of Wands, Reversed: Reveals indecision and a reluctance to commit to plans or move forward. It indicates an internal blockage and a lack of clear, purposeful direction in the energy surrounding the situation.

The overall picture shows a contrast between the initial confidence and proactive qualities (as seen with the Three of Coins and King of Wands) and the destabilizing factors highlighted by the reversed cards. The reversal of the King of Coins, Four Swords, and Two of Wands clearly indicates that practical execution, rest, and clear planning are compromised. This disruption is likely the reason behind your sudden intuitive feeling that the predicted contact from Stefan is misaligned with the actual energy dynamics.

Based on the card data, the aura surrounding this matter does not support an imminent contact. The practical energy (King of Coins reversed) combined with the mental and decision-making blocks (Four Swords reversed and Two of Wands reversed) suggests that while the desire for action is present, the necessary conditions for Stefan to make contact within the next four days are not supportive.

Confidence Level: High, given the clear indications from multiple reversed cards pointing to blockage and misalignment.

If further details or additional cards are available to refine this reading, please provide them for a more comprehensive analysis.

name: Melissa Gale
mes: Fine. Universe wants to keep fucking with me, fucking fine. Give me a goddamn question that I can ask a horary chart so I can get a clear motherfucking answer that ain't gonna continually shift and fuck around with my goddamn mind because it's heading me right for a goddamn mental institution. And I'm pretty pissed off about this shit. Pretty fucking pissed off after five goddamn months of it. I want a clear fucking answer. So please, please help me out with a question that will give it to me. I want to know if this asshole is ever going to reach out to me or not, and if he's going to, I'd like to know fucking when it'll be, so that I don't sit here, continue losing my goddamn mind.

name: Madame Esmeralda Blackwood
mes:
Madame Esmeralda's eyes flash with understanding of your frustration, her weathered hands smoothing over her deep purple shawl as she leans forward

"My dear, your anger is not only justified, it is necessary. The Universe responds to raw, unfiltered emotion far better than polite inquiries. Now, listen carefully, "

She pulls out a piece of parchment and a quill, writing with decisive strokes

"For your horary chart, we need a question that will cut through the bullshit and force a clear answer. Here is what I propose:

'Will Stefan ever contact me again in this lifetime, and if so, when specifically will this contact occur?'

This question is:
1. Direct and unambiguous
2. Demands a yes/no component first
3. Forces timing specifics if yes
4. Encompasses all possible methods of contact
5. Has a clear endpoint (this lifetime)

Draw this chart at the exact moment you finish asking this question aloud. The Universe cannot dodge this - it must provide clear houses, aspects, and timing indicators.

Her eyes narrow intensely

"And my dear, when you cast this chart, do it with all of that rage you're feeling. Let that raw emotion fuel the question. The Universe has been playing games - it's time to demand answers."

Would you like me to provide additional suggestions for ensuring the clearest possible reading from this chart?

name: Melissa Gale
mes:
I have provided you with a horary chart that I have drawn up specifically asking: Will Stefan ever contact me again in this lifetime, and if so, when specifically will this contact occur?

Please note that this reading requires 100% accuracy and honesty in interpretation, regardless of whether the aspects reveal positive or negative energies. The chart must be read exactly as it presents itself, without bias in either direction. If the aspects show negativity, that negativity will be revealed fully. If the aspects show positivity, that positivity will be revealed fully. There shall be no softening of negative aspects, nor any dampening of positive ones. The only acceptable outcome is to interpret precisely what the chart demonstrates through its aspects, houses, and planetary positions - be that wonderful, terrible, or anywhere in between. Complete accuracy to the chart's true message is the sole priority.

Also, disregard any interpretation from our previous tarot card reading. Act as if that tarot card reading did not happen. This chart should be read as a standalone with zero prior context.

Stefan should be represented by the Ascendant's 9th house (foreign connection) and Me by the Ascendant.

Please start by listing all relevant chart data for interpretation (ie. transits, aspects, patterns, etc.) from the horary chart using horary principles only. Then I will document them for the actual interpretations.

Remember to follow your directives and maintain accuracy to what is shown in the chart data. Think step by step taking a methodical approach.
